<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/img/weather-cloud.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css" />
</head>

<body>
    <div class="main-content">
        {{>header}}

        <div class="goodBoiArea">
            <p>If you're feeling sad about your weather, just look at this <a class="puppyLink"
                    href="https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Good%20boi" target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener">good
                    boi</a> :)</p>
            <img class="portrait" src="/img/puppy.jpg" alt="puppy">
        </div>

        <div class="disclaimer">
            <p>The weather data used on this website is fetched from <a href="https://weatherstack.com/" target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener">Weatherstack</a>. The location data is provided by
                <a href="https://www.mapbox.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mapbox</a>. The news are supplied by <a
                    href="https://newsapi.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">News API</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="stackDetails">
            <p>The stack used:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>HTML & CSS (duh, obviously)</li>
                <li>Node.js</li>
                <li>Express.js</li>
                <li>Weatherstack API (weather data)</li>
                <li>Mapbox API (location data)</li>
                <li>News API</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    {{>footer}}
</body>

</html>